The new governor of Nasarawa State, Abdullahi Sule, says he is not in a hurry to appoint members of his cabinet. Speaking in Lafia, the governor said, “I will not be in a hurry to appoint my commissioners because doing that will lead me into making mistakes.” According to him, “I just started working on Thursday and we are studying the handover book. I have also started meeting with all the permanent secretaries, government agencies and different people.” Engr. Sule said he met and discussed with some local government chairmen and security agencies on the way towards improving security for people in the state and ensure they lived in peace with one another. I am not in a hurry to appoint my cabinet – Nasarawa governor Only competent politicians will make my cabinet – Nasarawa Gov-elect Only competent politicians’ll make my cabinet — Nasarawa gov-elect Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin